    "updated_at": "2013-10-10T12:18:23Z",
    "body": "This is probably because `epoll` (or any blocking syscall, really) blocks an entire real thread, not just a rust task. As a workaround, you might be able to use\n\n```\nstd::task::spawn_sched(std::task::SingleThreaded, fun);\n```\n\nto get a real OS thread per newly spawned task.\n",
